---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero fade-in">
      <h1>Christophe Trefois</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Head of Technology | Luxembourg National Data Service</p>
      <p class="description">
        Leading technology innovation and AI infrastructure development for Luxembourg's national data ecosystem. 
        Expert in large-scale data infrastructure, genomic data federation, and building GDPR-compliant platforms 
        with a focus on enabling cutting-edge research and innovation.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <a href="/about" class="btn">Learn More</a>
        <a href="/publications" class="btn btn-outline">View Publications</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-outline">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Current Role</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Head of Technology, LNDS Luxembourg</h3>
        <p><strong>Since November 2022</strong></p>
        <p>
          Leading the technology team at Luxembourg National Data Service, I oversee the design, development, 
          and operation of data infrastructure that enables secure secondary use of public sector data. Our work 
          focuses on building trustable platforms for data sharing, implementing FAIR data principles, and supporting 
          Luxembourg's digital transformation strategy.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <strong>Key responsibilities include:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.8;">
          <li>Leading a multidisciplinary team of data, software, DevOps, security, and infrastructure engineers</li>
          <li>Architecting secure processing environments and federated data access platforms</li>
          <li>Overseeing development of data services including cataloguing, pseudonymization, and synthetic data generation</li>
          <li>Contributing to European data space initiatives and the European Health Data Space</li>
          <li>Establishing partnerships with organizations like DFKI for AI collaboration and ERTICO for smart mobility</li>
          <li>Ensuring data protection by design and GDPR compliance across all technical solutions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Expertise & Focus Areas</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>ü§ñ AI Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Leading Luxembourg's AI Factory initiative to democratize access to artificial intelligence capabilities for research and industry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>üß¨ Genomic Data Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Leading WP4 of the European GDI project, building federated infrastructure for secure genomic data access across 24 countries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>üíª Data Platforms</h3>
          <p>Building scalable, GDPR-compliant platforms for biomedical data analysis, storage, and sharing across institutions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>üîí Data Governance</h3>
          <p>Expertise in data protection, consent management, and building compliant research data infrastructure (DAISY project).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>üîÑ Reproducible Research</h3>
          <p>Developing tools and frameworks for ensuring reproducibility in computational research and data science.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>ü§ù Open Science</h3>
          <p>Promoting FAIR data principles, open access, and transparent research practices through European initiatives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Career Highlights</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>2014 - 2022: Luxembourg Centre for Systems Biomedicine (LCSB)</h3>
          <p><strong>Bioinformatics Core Group</strong></p>
          <ul style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <li>Led bioinformatics infrastructure development</li>
            <li>Deputy Technical Coordinator of ELIXIR Luxembourg (2017-2022)</li>
            <li>Developed GDPR-compliant data management systems</li>
            <li>Coordinated multi-institutional research projects</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>2010 - 2014: PhD in Systems Biology</h3>
          <p><strong>LCSB, University of Luxembourg</strong></p>
          <ul style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <li>Research on Parkinson's disease molecular mechanisms</li>
            <li>Developed computational models for disease progression</li>
            <li>Visiting researcher at Institute for Systems Biology, Seattle</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>2008 - 2010: Ernst & Young Luxembourg</h3>
          <p><strong>IT Consultant & IT Auditor</strong></p>
          <ul style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <li>IT consulting for financial and industrial sectors</li>
            <li>IT security and compliance auditing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>2008: MSc in Communication Systems</h3>
          <p><strong>EPFL (Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Lausanne)</strong></p>
          <ul style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <li>Master thesis at SAP Labs France on wireless sensor networks security</li>
            <li>Focus on distributed systems and network security</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Key Projects & Initiatives</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Luxembourg AI Factory</h3>
          <p>Principal Investigator leading Luxembourg's national AI infrastructure to accelerate AI adoption across research and industry sectors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>GDI Project (WP4 Leader)</h3>
          <p>Leading Work Package 4 of the ‚Ç¨40M European Genomic Data Infrastructure project, creating federated access to genomic data.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>ELIXIR Luxembourg</h3>
          <p>Former Deputy Technical Coordinator contributing to Europe's life science data infrastructure and sustainable data management.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>DAISY Platform</h3>
          <p>Developed comprehensive GDPR-compliant data management system for biomedical research, enabling accountability and transparency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Recognition & Service</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 2;">
          <li><strong>Mendeley Advisor</strong> (since 2011) - Supporting researchers in reference management</li>
          <li><strong>Program Committee Member</strong> - Multiple international conferences (DILS 2017, ICT Innovations 2018-2019, ICT 2019)</li>
          <li><strong>Invited Speaker</strong> - Conferences on bioinformatics, data management, and reproducible research</li>
          <li><strong>Workshop Organizer</strong> - Big Data & Medicine, GDPR compliance, standardization in life sciences</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

